ilk into mixing bowl and heat <b>10 min\/37°C\/speed 1<b>."},{"content":"Place junket tablets and 1 tbsp water into a separate bowl and stir to combine."},{"content":"Add junket mixture into mixing bowl and combine <b>1 min\/speed 1<b>. Transfer milk into a thermal serving bowl or other large bowl, cover and set aside for 1 hour. Clean and dry mixing bowl."},{"content":"Cut curds into strips (2 cm) each way at a 45° angle. Allow to sit for another 10 minutes for curds and whey to develop further."},{"content":"Place curds and whey into mixing bowl and heat <b>30 min\/37°C\/speed <b>."},{"content":"Place simmering basket over a jug and line simmering basket with cheese cloth. Transfer curds and whey into cheese cloth. Fold overhanging cheese cloth over curds and whey to cover. Place a heavy weight (such as a can of beans) on top of curds and whey. Set aside for 30 minutes to allow whey to drain. Clean and dry mixing bowl."},{"content":"Place whey from jug into mixing bowl and heat <b>5 min\/90°C\/speed 1<b>."},{"content":"Remove curds from cheese cloth and cut into slices (1 cm thick). Discard cheese cloth and place curds back into simmering basket. Insert simmering basket into mixing bowl and cook <b>30 min\/90°C\/speed <b>, or until haloumi pieces rise to the top of the liquid."},{"content":"Set simmering basket aside and allow haloumi to cool."},{"content":"Transfer whey into a jug and set aside."},{"content":"Place water and salt into mixing bowl and heat for <b>3 min\/100°C\/speed 1<b>."},{"content":"Add 250 g of the reserved whey and cook <b>5 min\/100°C\/speed 1<b>. Transfer into a sealable container and set aside to cool."},{"content":"Add haloumi to brine mixture and place into refrigerator until ready to serve. Clean and dry mixing bowl."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Salad dressing"},{"content":"Place garlic into mixing bowl and chop <b>3 sec\/speed 7<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula."},{"content":"Add all remaining salad dressing ingredi